        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 13 at 4:08PM CDT by NWS Jackson MS</headline>
        <description>At 408 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Blackwater, or 7 miles south of De Kalb, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Meridian Station, Daleville, Blackwater, and Prismatic around 415
PM CDT.
Meridian, Lauderdale, and Tamola around 430 PM CDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
